    • getParent

      public Person getParent​(char type) throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
      The getter method for the person's parent(s). This method returns either the mother or the father; not both. Mother is denoted by 'M' and father is denoted by 'F'.
      Parameters:
      type - the type of parent the you want to get denoted by char 'M' or 'F'
      Returns:
      the parent as selected for by the argument passed to the method
      Throws:
      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the argument is not a character 'F' or 'M'.

    • setParent

      public void setParent​(char type, Person parent) throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
      The setter method for the person's parent(s). This method sets either the mother or the father; not both. Mother is denoted by 'M' and father is denoted by 'F'.
      Parameters:
      type - the type of parent the you want to set denoted by char 'M' or 'F'
      parent - either the mother or the father of this person
      Throws:
      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the argument is not a character 'F' or 'M'.
